annotations:
  - {"kind":"user","id":"7d61322c-9ab7-4ca3-860b-78f99980e0ef","message":"Explain to me how the messages sidebar is composed; please annotate the verious files involved.","preset":"%Q","scope":"line","anchor":{"line":14,"text":"import { promptPresets, type PromptContext, type PromptPreset, type PromptScope } from '../../promptCommand.js';","before":["} from '../../agentProtocol.js';","import { isAnnotation, type AgentFileAnnotation, type Annotation, type AnnotationLink, type UserAnnotation } from '../../annotationProtocol.js';","import { maximumPaneSplitPercent, minimumPaneSplitPercent } from '../../paneSplit.js';"],"after":["export interface HostNotice {","\treadonly tone: 'info' | 'error';","\treadonly message: string;"]},"officialResponses":[{"userAnnotationId":"7d61322c-9ab7-4ca3-860b-78f99980e0ef","agentId":"ce1e8a00-b1b7-4f99-9a0c-6f4ad4f0468c","agentSessionId":"992c5328-6640-43c2-9aa3-8249a3f59cf2","body":"## How the Messages sidebar is composed\n\nThe **Messages** sidebar is a VS Code `WebviewView`, not a native Tree View. It has two runtime halves:\n\n1. **VS Code extension host:** owns editor integration, CLI-backed state, work lifecycle actions, and the webview bridge.\n2. **Webview browser bundle:** a Lit custom element that renders agents, the composer, history, and the annotation viewer from host-provided state.\n\n### Composition path\n\n- **`packages/editor/package.json`** — contributes the `sundialEditor` container to VS Code’s `secondarySidebar`, then contributes `sundialEditor.messages` inside it as a `webview`. It also activates the extension when that view is opened and defines the persisted pane-split setting.\n- **`packages/editor/src/extension.ts`** — creates `MessagesWebviewProvider` and registers it for that view ID. It also tracks active-editor/selection changes, watches `.sundial/**/*.comments`, and supplies callbacks that reveal source locations and display annotation markers.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/messages/messagesWebviewProvider.ts`** — the host-side coordinator. When VS Code resolves the view, `resolveWebviewView` enables scripts, attaches the validated message router, and produces the initial HTML. The provider loads agents and queued work through `cliRunner`, reads annotations for the active source file, starts or controls agent work, and republishes a complete state snapshot after changes.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/shared/csp.ts`** — renders the HTML shell. It installs the `se-messages-app` element, embeds the initial state as escaped JSON, loads the locally bundled `dist/webviews/messages.js`, and applies a nonce-based restrictive CSP.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/messages/messages.ts`** — the shared boundary contract. `MessagesState` is the data model rendered by the client; `HostToWebview` and `WebviewToHost` enumerate allowed messages, while runtime guards reject malformed input. It also contains presentation and selection helpers for agent work and annotations.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/shared/messageRouter.ts`** — validates inbound browser messages before dispatching them to the provider and exposes the host-to-client posting function.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/apps/messages/index.ts`** — browser entry point; it registers the Lit component.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/apps/messages/messages-app.ts`** — `MessagesApp`, the Lit UI. In its ordinary layout it renders an Agents pane above an Annotation viewer, separated by an accessible, keyboard- and pointer-resizable divider. It switches to takeover views for composing a prompt, viewing an agent’s status history, or expanding an annotation. `applyHostMessage` consumes host state; click, form, navigation, and resize handlers emit typed actions back to the provider.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/apps/messages/markdown.ts`** — renders annotation responses with Markdown-It configured to disable raw HTML; the Lit component inserts that generated HTML for response bodies.\n- **`packages/editor/src/webviews/apps/shared/host.ts`** — wraps VS Code’s `acquireVsCodeApi`, including the persisted webview state used for fast restoration.\n\n### Data and interaction flow\n\n`extension.ts` → `MessagesWebviewProvider` → CSP HTML shell → `MessagesApp` is the startup path. The provider sends `{ kind: 'state', state }`; the client stores and renders it. Client actions such as submit, refresh, rename, open/reset/interrupt agent, annotation navigation, deletion, and pane resizing travel back as `WebviewToHost` messages. The provider validates and dispatches each action, calls the CLI-backed services where appropriate, refreshes state, and sends the next snapshot.\n\nThe source-specific annotations were added at:\n\n- `packages/editor/package.json:52` — sidebar/view contribution.\n- `packages/editor/src/extension.ts:21` — extension-host composition root.\n- `packages/editor/src/webviews/messages/messages.ts:15` — shared typed protocol and state boundary.\n- `packages/editor/src/webviews/apps/messages/messages-app.ts:754` — Lit layout and takeover composition.\n\n### Validation\n\n- Performed read-only source tracing across the contribution manifest, extension registration, provider, webview HTML/CSP helper, message router, shared protocol, and Lit application.\n- Ran `git diff --check` successfully.\n- No product code was changed and no test suite was needed for this explanatory request.\n\nThe explanation follows the applicable webview decisions: WebviewView sidebar composition (DR-0009), provider/client separation and typed messages (DR-0004 and DR-0008), Lit client use (DR-0003), and strict CSP bootstrapping (DR-0005).\n","createdAt":"2026-07-21T12:06:19.938Z"}],"agentAnnotations":[{"annotationId":"agent-b104d2e3ab22d6f24c76ba3a640203b2","file":"packages/editor/package.json","line":51},{"annotationId":"agent-0fa3361209608a15a1d46ac2ef74f9a9","file":"packages/editor/src/extension.ts","line":20},{"annotationId":"agent-bd3f310951874f2a22b1ed65b157c252","file":"packages/editor/src/webviews/messages/messages.ts","line":14},{"annotationId":"agent-b2976c318ce84ae43d4283b9cfb92aa8","file":"packages/editor/src/webviews/apps/messages/messages-app.ts","line":753}]}
  - {"kind":"agent","id":"agent-bd3f310951874f2a22b1ed65b157c252","agentId":"ce1e8a00-b1b7-4f99-9a0c-6f4ad4f0468c","agentSessionId":"992c5328-6640-43c2-9aa3-8249a3f59cf2","body":"## Host/client boundary\n\nThis module is deliberately shared by the extension host and browser bundle. `MessagesState` is the host-owned snapshot rendered by the sidebar; the two discriminated unions below describe every allowed message in each direction and runtime guards reject malformed inbound data.\n\nKeeping this contract separate lets the Lit UI remain a renderer and event sender rather than reaching into VS Code or the CLI directly.\n","createdAt":"2026-07-21T12:05:48.839Z","anchor":{"line":14,"text":"import { promptPresets, type PromptContext, type PromptPreset, type PromptScope } from '../../promptCommand.js';","before":["} from '../../agentProtocol.js';","import { isAnnotation, type AgentFileAnnotation, type Annotation, type AnnotationLink, type UserAnnotation } from '../../annotationProtocol.js';","import { maximumPaneSplitPercent, minimumPaneSplitPercent } from '../../paneSplit.js';"],"after":["export interface HostNotice {","\treadonly tone: 'info' | 'error';","\treadonly message: string;"]},"userAnnotation":{"annotationId":"7d61322c-9ab7-4ca3-860b-78f99980e0ef","file":"packages/editor/src/webviews/messages/messages.ts","line":14}}
